    Expand With Mzroll Defaults

    expand_with_mzroll_defaults.Rd

    Expand With Mzroll Defaults

    expand_with_mzroll_defaults(mzroll_data)

    Arguments

    mzroll_data

    a list of tables corresponding to an mzrollDB SQL schema, but possibly missing some variables.

    Value

    mzroll_data with default values added for variables which were not initially included

    Examples

    library(dplyr)

peakgroups <- tibble::tibble(groupId = 1:10, compoundName = LETTERS[1:10])
samples <- tibble::tibble(sampleId = 1:10)
peaks <- tidyr::crossing(peakgroups, samples) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(peakId = 1:dplyr::n())

mzroll_data <- list(
  peakgroups = peakgroups,
  samples = samples,
  peaks = peaks
)

expand_with_mzroll_defaults(mzroll_data)
